 qemu-server (9.1.14) trixie; urgency=medium
 
   * cpu config: expose the QEMU 'level' property. Windows guests with Hyper-V
     enabled fail to boot with certain CPU types like 'host' or 'max' on recent
     Intel CPUs unless 'level=30' is set; the workaround previously required
     custom 'args', which then lost other Proxmox VE CPU configuration. Expose
     it as a first-class property instead.
 
   * volume rescan: also consider volumes that storage plugins list with only
     an approximate size, so 'qm rescan' picks up inactive qcow2 LVs on LVM for
